HEADWORD: Triplication
<hw>Trip"li*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>triplicatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>triplication</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of tripling, or making threefold, or adding
three together.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Civil Law)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Surrejoinder</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triplicity</ent>⟦br⟧
